comment:
* Parameters for QoS policies requested by system applications.
 * @hide

variables.name: DSCP_ANY
variables.comment: * Indicates that the policy does not specify a DSCP value.

variables.name: PROTOCOL_ANY
variables.comment: * Indicates that the policy does not specify a protocol.

variables.name: PROTOCOL_TCP
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets using the TCP protocol.

variables.name: PROTOCOL_UDP
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets using the UDP protocol.

variables.name: PROTOCOL_ESP
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets using the ESP protocol.

variables.name: DIRECTION_UPLINK
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets in the uplink direction.

variables.name: DIRECTION_DOWNLINK
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets in the downlink direction.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_ANY
variables.comment: * Indicates that the policy does not specify a User Priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_BACKGROUND_LOW
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a low background priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_BACKGROUND_HIGH
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a high background priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_BEST_EFFORT_LOW
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a low best-effort priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_BEST_EFFORT_HIGH
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a high best-effort priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_VIDEO_LOW
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a low video priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_VIDEO_HIGH
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a high video priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_VOICE_LOW
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a low voice priority.

variables.name: USER_PRIORITY_VOICE_HIGH
variables.comment: * Policy should be assigned a high voice priority.

variables.name: IP_VERSION_ANY
variables.comment: * Indicates that the policy does not specify an IP version.

variables.name: IP_VERSION_4
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets using IPv4.

variables.name: IP_VERSION_6
variables.comment: * Policy should match packets using IPv6.

variables.name: DESTINATION_PORT_ANY
variables.comment: * Indicates that the policy does not specify a destination port.

variables.name: mPolicyId
variables.comment: * Unique policy ID. See {@link Builder#Builder(int, int)} for more information.

variables.name: mTranslatedPolicyId
variables.comment:
* Translated policy ID. Should only be set by the Wi-Fi service.
     * @hide

variables.name: mDscp
variables.comment: QoS DSCP marking. See {@link Builder#setDscp(int)} for more information.

variables.name: mUserPriority
variables.comment: User priority to apply to packets matching the policy. Only applicable to downlink requests.

variables.name: mSrcIp
variables.comment: Source IP address.

variables.name: mDstIp
variables.comment: Destination IP address.

variables.name: mSrcPort
variables.comment: Source port.

variables.name: mProtocol
variables.comment: IP protocol that the policy requires.

variables.name: mDstPort
variables.comment: Single destination port. Only applicable to downlink requests.

variables.name: mDstPortRange
variables.comment: Destination port range. Inclusive range. Only applicable to uplink requests.

variables.name: mDirection
variables.comment: Direction of traffic stream.

variables.name: mIpVersion
variables.comment: IP version. Only applicable to downlink requests.

variables.name: mFlowLabel
variables.comment: Flow label. Only applicable to downlink requests using IPv6.

variables.name: mQosCharacteristics
variables.comment: QoS characteristics. Mandatory for uplink requests.

methods.name: public boolean validate()
methods.comment:
* Validate the parameters in this instance.
     *
     * @return true if all parameters are valid, false otherwise
     * @hide

methods.name: public void setTranslatedPolicyId(int translatedPolicyId)
methods.comment:
* Set the translated policy ID for this policy.
     *
     * Note: Translated policy IDs should only be set by the Wi-Fi service.
     * @hide

methods.name: public int getPolicyId()
methods.comment:
* Get the ID for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#Builder(int, int)} for more information.

methods.name: public int getTranslatedPolicyId()
methods.comment:
* Get the translated ID for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link #setTranslatedPolicyId} for more information.
     * @hide

methods.name: public int getDscp()
methods.comment:
* Get the DSCP value for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setDscp(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return DSCP value, or {@link #DSCP_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public int getUserPriority()
methods.comment:
* Get the User Priority (UP) for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setUserPriority(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return User Priority value, or {@link #USER_PRIORITY_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public InetAddress getSourceAddress()
methods.comment:
* Get the source IP address for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setSourceAddress(InetAddress)} for more information.
     *
     * @return source IP address, or null if not assigned.

methods.name: public InetAddress getDestinationAddress()
methods.comment:
* Get the destination IP address for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setDestinationAddress(InetAddress)} for more information.
     *
     * @return destination IP address, or null if not assigned.

methods.name: public int getSourcePort()
methods.comment:
* Get the source port for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setSourcePort(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return source port, or {@link DscpPolicy#SOURCE_PORT_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public int getProtocol()
methods.comment:
* Get the protocol for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setProtocol(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return protocol, or {@link #PROTOCOL_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public int getDestinationPort()
methods.comment:
* Get the destination port for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setDestinationPort(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return destination port, or {@link #DESTINATION_PORT_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public int[] getDestinationPortRange()
methods.comment:
* Get the destination port range for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setDestinationPortRange(int, int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return destination port range, or null if not assigned.

methods.name: public int getDirection()
methods.comment:
* Get the direction for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#Builder(int, int)} for more information.

methods.name: public int getIpVersion()
methods.comment:
* Get the IP version for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setIpVersion(int)} for more information.
     *
     * @return IP version, or {@link #IP_VERSION_ANY} if not assigned.

methods.name: public byte[] getFlowLabel()
methods.comment:
* Get the flow label for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setFlowLabel(byte[])} for more information.
     *
     * @return flow label, or null if not assigned.

methods.name: public QosCharacteristics getQosCharacteristics()
methods.comment:
* Get the QoS characteristics for this policy.
     *
     * See {@link Builder#setQosCharacteristics(QosCharacteristics)} for more information.
     *
     * @return QoS characteristics object, or null if not assigned.
